But Roy Williams, the current North Carolina coach who spent 10 years as Smith's assistant also paid tribute to him.

He said: 'He was the greatest there ever was on the court, but far, far, better off the court with people.'

'I'd like to say on behalf of all our players and coaches, past and present, that Dean Smith was the perfect picture of what a college basketball coach should have been. We love him and we will miss him,' Williams added.

Smith coached the Tar Heels from 1961-97. He retired after winning the most in the sport with 879 victories. 

In 1982 and 1983 he won NCAA titles and coached such players as Michael Jordan and James Worthy.

